---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Integrations from '../components/Integrations.astro';
import Pricing from '../components/Pricing.astro';
---
<Layout title="Earned media for university enrollment" description="Earned media for university enrollment — the earned-media engine for higher education. Be the answer in AI, the result in Google, and the name in the press.">
<!-- HERO -->
<header class="ind-hero" id="top">
  <div class="hero-atmos"><div class="grid"></div><div class="glow g1"></div><div class="glow g2"></div><div class="glow g3"></div></div>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="ind-eyebrow"><a class="bk" href="index.html">701am for Higher&nbsp;Ed</a> / For universities, colleges &amp; online programs</div>
    <h1>Be the program students <em class="grad">find first</em>.</h1>
    <p class="isub">Applicants now ask ChatGPT and Google “what’s the best program for X” months before they ever request information. 701am makes your program the answer — with the rankings, outcomes data, and earned coverage that drive AI citations, search visibility, and enrollment. <b>Built by a team that’s spent a decade in education visibility.</b></p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <button class="btn btn-primary btn-lg js-soon"><i class="ti ti-sparkles"></i>Request early access</button>
      <button class="btn btn-soft btn-lg js-soon"><i class="ti ti-player-play"></i>See it work</button>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-stat"><b>Most</b> applicants now shortlist programs via AI and search before they ever inquire</div>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- NAMED PROBLEM -->
<section class="band wrap">
  <div class="problem">
    <div class="problem-eyebrow">The discovery problem</div>
    <h2 class="problem-h">Students choose from a <em class="grad">shortlist</em> built before you knew they existed.<br><span class="problem-until">701am gets you on it.</span></h2>
    <p class="problem-p">Enrollment now begins with a search and an AI answer, months before an inquiry form. If your program isn’t in the “best online MBA” list ChatGPT recites, or the rankings Google surfaces, you’re invisible at the exact moment the decision narrows. 701am earns the rankings, the data stories, and the third-party coverage that put you on the shortlist — compounding season over season instead of resetting every cycle.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- LANDSCAPE -->
<section class="band wrap">
  <div class="sec-head">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">The landscape</div>
    <h2>How programs get discovered now.</h2>
    <p>Generic PR treats every client the same. 701am works the channels that actually confer credibility in higher ed.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="landscape">
    <div class="lscard">
      <div class="li" style="background:var(--gold-soft);color:var(--gold-deep)"><i class="ti ti-trophy"></i></div>
      <h3>Rankings &amp; “best of” lists</h3><p>The ranking sites and “best program” round-ups applicants check first — and that AI models quote verbatim.</p><span class="lq">AI asks: <b>“best [degree] program?”</b></span>
    </div>
    <div class="lscard">
      <div class="li" style="background:var(--coral-soft);color:var(--coral-deep)"><i class="ti ti-chart-histogram"></i></div>
      <h3>Outcomes &amp; ROI data</h3><p>Salary outcomes, completion rates, ROI studies — the numbers that earn coverage and that applicants actually weigh.</p><span class="lq">Cited as <b>the program stat</b></span>
    </div>
    <div class="lscard">
      <div class="li" style="background:var(--indigo-soft);color:var(--indigo-deep)"><i class="ti ti-news"></i></div>
      <h3>Higher-ed &amp; regional press</h3><p>Inside Higher Ed, EdSurge, and the regional outlets that confer legitimacy on a program or institution.</p><span class="lq">Becomes the <b>credible source</b></span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
<section class="band wrap">
  <div class="sec-head">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">How it works</div>
    <h2>Connect. Set. <em class="grad">Compound.</em></h2>
    <p>Four steps from your institutional data to visibility that builds every enrollment cycle.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="how-steps">
    <div class="how-step">
      <div class="hs-num">1</div>
      <h3>Connect your data</h3>
      <p>Link Slate, Ellucian, Workday, or upload outcomes directly. Read-only — the engine works from your existing institutional records.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="how-step">
      <div class="hs-num">2</div>
      <h3>Set your program goal</h3>
      <p>Tell it which programs you want to grow and where you compete. The swarm builds a baseline of your current AI, search, and press position.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="how-step">
      <div class="hs-num">3</div>
      <h3>The swarm runs</h3>
      <p>Researching angles, writing pitches, earning coverage — continuously. Every placement feeds your visibility across AI citations, search rankings, and press mentions.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="how-step">
      <div class="hs-num">4</div>
      <h3>Watch it compound</h3>
      <p>A placement this season feeds the AI answer next season. A ranking earned once keeps paying out. Visibility builds instead of resets.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- COMPARISON -->
<section class="band wrap">
  <div class="sec-head">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">How we compare</div>
    <h2>701am vs. the <em class="grad">alternatives</em>.</h2>
    <p>For a fraction of what a PR retainer costs, you get an engine that compounds instead of resets.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="compare">
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th></th><th>Traditional PR agency</th><th>701am</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Monthly cost</td><td>$8K–$15K+</td><td>From $1,500</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Output type</td><td>Hours billed</td><td>Visibility that compounds</td></tr>
        <tr><td>AI citation tracking</td><td><span class="no">&mdash;</span></td><td><span class="chk">✓</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Rankings &amp; "best of" coverage</td><td>Ad-hoc</td><td><span class="chk">✓</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Timed to application calendar</td><td>When retainer allows</td><td><span class="chk">✓</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>CRM funnel correlation</td><td><span class="no">&mdash;</span></td><td><span class="chk">✓</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Performance</td><td>Resets per campaign</td><td>Compounds every cycle</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- DATA STORY -->
<section class="band wrap">
  <div class="sec-head">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">What it produces</div>
    <h2>A story a reporter <em class="grad">actually opens</em>.</h2>
    <p>Not a press release. A data-backed angle built from real numbers — the kind that earns coverage and gets cited.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="story">
    <div class="story-h"><i class="ti ti-file-text"></i>Campaign angle<span class="mono">auto-generated · example</span></div>
    <div class="story-b">
      <div class="hl">“Graduates of online programs out-earned on-campus peers by 14% in three fields — led by nursing”</div>
      <div class="meta"><span class="m">Archetype: Outcomes index</span><span class="m">Source: IPEDS + Census</span><span class="m">Beats: Higher ed + regional</span><span class="m live">Status: Reporter-ready</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- WHO IT'S FOR -->
<section class="band wrap">
  <div class="sec-head">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Who it’s for</div>
    <h2>Built for teams like <em class="grad">yours</em>.</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="forwho">
    <div class="fw"><i class="ti ti-school"></i><span class="ft"><b>Online &amp; graduate programs</b> competing for enrollment on “best program” queries</span></div>
    <div class="fw"><i class="ti ti-building-community"></i><span class="ft"><b>Colleges &amp; universities</b> whose outcomes data could anchor real coverage and rankings</span></div>
    <div class="fw"><i class="ti ti-target-arrow"></i><span class="ft"><b>Enrollment &amp; marketing teams</b> who need visibility timed to the application calendar</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FLAGSHIP DEPTH (universities) -->
<section class="band wrap">
  <div class="sec-head">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Why us, for enrollment</div>
    <h2>We’ve spent a decade in <em class="grad">education visibility</em>.</h2>
    <p>This isn’t a vertical we bolted on. It’s where 701am’s team has lived for years — and it shows in how the engine thinks about enrollment.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="forwho">
    <div class="fw"><i class="ti ti-trophy"></i><span class="ft">We understand <b>rankings as a channel</b> — how “best program” lists form, who reads them, and how AI now repeats them.</span></div>
    <div class="fw"><i class="ti ti-chart-histogram"></i><span class="ft">We know which <b>outcomes data</b> earns coverage — salary lift, completion, ROI — because we’ve built the studies that landed it.</span></div>
    <div class="fw"><i class="ti ti-calendar-event"></i><span class="ft">We build around the <b>application calendar</b>, not a generic content cadence — visibility timed to when applicants actually decide.</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- INTEGRATIONS -->
<Integrations context="universities" />

<!-- PRICING -->
<Pricing context="universities" />

<!-- CLOSING -->
<section class="closing">
  <div class="catmos"><div class="cg"></div></div>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="pill-badge"><span class="tagm">Filed at sunrise</span></div>
    <h2>Be impossible to <em class="grad">miss</em>.</h2>
    <p>701am is opening to a first group of higher-ed teams. Put your name down.</p>
    <button class="btn btn-primary btn-lg js-soon"><i class="ti ti-sparkles"></i>Request early access</button>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>
